text: Millmerran Woods is a locality in the Toowoomba Region, Queensland, Australia. In the , Millmerran Woods had a population of 92 people. == Geography == Millmerran Woods is a rural residential area with large acreage properties. == History == The locality name is derived from the nearby town of Millmerran, which in turn is derived from Aboriginal words in the Gooneburra language with meel meaning eye and merran meaning lookout. == Education == There are no schools in Millmerran Woods. The nearest primary and secondary school to Year 10 is in Millmerran and the nearest secondary school to Year 12 in is Pittsworth. == References == Category:Toowoomba Region Category:Localities in Queensland
